hey i'm working on a shopify theme and the product image is overlapping the title on mobile but looks fine on desktop. can u look at this css and tell me why it's breaking?

.product-container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  padding: 20px;
}

.product-image {
  width: 50%;
}

.product-info {
  width: 50%;
}

@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {
  .product-container {
    display: block;
  }
  .product-image {
    width: 100%;
  }
  .product-info {
    width: 100%;
  }
}

The issue you're facing with the product image overlapping the title on mobile devices is likely due to the "display: flex;" property on the ".product-container" class. This property causes the child elements to align side by side, which can lead to overlapping on smaller screens. To fix this, you can change the display property to "block" for smaller screens, which will stack the elements vertically. Additionally, you might want to adjust the widths of the child elements to ensure they don't grow disproportionately on smaller screens. Here's a revised version of your CSS:

```css
/* Before Media Query */
@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {
  .product-container {
    display: block; /* Stacks the child elements vertically */
  }
  .product-image,
  .product-info {
    width: 100%; /* Takes full width of the container */
    margin-bottom: 10px; /* Add some space between stacked items */
  }
}
```

